    "description": "Chained Track A plan: three sequential calibration steps produce the full set of credit-pricing curves in a single calibrate() call. Step 1 bootstraps the USD-OIS discount curve from deposit and IRS quotes (same quotes as 01_usd_discount.json). Step 2 calibrates the CDX.NA.IG.46 index hazard curve from par-spread CDS quotes using very tight sub-1bp spreads (0.06/0.15/0.32/0.44/0.60 bp at 1Y/3Y/5Y/7Y/10Y), producing SP(5Y)≈0.9997 characteristic of a near-zero default probability environment. Step 3 solves for the CDX-IG-46 base correlation smile from 5 tranche upfront quotes that are self-consistent with the step-2 bootstrapped hazard (quotes were generated by pricing each tranche against the chained market with a representative seed correlation of 0.10–0.55). FX cross rates (EUR/USD, USD/JPY, GBP/USD) are carried in initial_market.fx as a snapshot — they are not bootstrapped but survive into the final MarketContext unchanged. Placeholder discount and hazard curves in initial_market are overwritten by steps 1 and 2. A seed base_correlation curve and credit_indices entry in initial_market are required by the base correlation solver (see 05_cdx_base_correlation.json for explanation). This is the canonical 'analyst's morning bootstrap' for a credit desk — one envelope, one calibrate() call, produces the full set of credit-pricing curves plus FX.",
